Kenyan champions drawn against Zambia’s Napsa in play-offs for group stage of tourneyOchieng’ , who has been handling the team together with team manager Jolawi Obondo and youth team coach Jared Odongo, said K’Ogalo had a good chance of advancing but only with good preparationsGor’s Ugandan-born striker Tito Okello also told Nation Sport that the draw was favourable to them Record champions Gor Mahia are expected to name a new coach on Sunday to handle them in Kenya and Africa. 

At the same time, members of the team expressed confidence in getting past Napsa of Zambian in the CAF Confederation Cup playoffs slated for next month.The draw was conducted in Cairo on Friday. 

“We expect a foreign coach will be in the touchline this weekend. He is expected to arrive on Sunday morning and he will oversee our preparations for the Confederation Cup playoffs,” said goalkeeper trainer Willis Ochieng’ . 



