“We are sure of reaching the group stages but with thorough preparations devoid of strikes and go-slows caused by delay in paying salaries. 

“Gor have a good squad now, and some of the players in Napsa camp were with us therefore we can say we know a few things about them,” said Ochieng’. 

Former K’Ogalo duo of Timothy Otieno and custodian Shaban Odhoji are currently with Napsa. 

Former Mathare United player Andrew Tololwa also plies his trade with the Zambian Premier League side that is in the process of acquiring the services of Kenya international David Owino “Calaber”, another  former Gor Mahia defender. 

Gor’s Ugandan-born striker Tito Okello also told Nation Sport that the draw was favourable to them. 

“It is important we win at home. We should also avoid conceding easy goals. Despite the recent heavy defeat, we have to stay focused,” said Okello. 



