From left: Gor Mahia players Tito Okello, Benson Omala and Kelvin Wesonga attend a training session at Nyayo National Stadium on December 4, 2020, on the eve of their Caf Champions League preliminary round return match against APR of Rwanda.
Photo credit: Sila Kiplagat | Nation Media Group

 

K'ogalo will be at home in the first leg slated for February 14 with the reverse fixture in Zambia on February 21. 

Gor were bundled out of the CAF Champions League in first round by CR Belouizdad of Algeria 8-1 on aggregate. 

The Kenyan champions had seen off familiar opponents APR of Rwanda in the preliminary round 4-3 on aggregate. 

Napsa are currently 16th in the 18-club Zambian Premier League table on seven points, 13 behind leaders Prison Leopards. 

Without a coach and assistant and with the players on strike, Gor Mahia management will be hard pressed to smooth matters at the club. 

A juicy carrot for the players is a guarantee of Sh27 million for the club from Caf as prize money for advancing to the group stage. 

The club has already settled one month salary out of the two owed to the playing unit. 

Gor have had mixed fortunes in the Confederation Cup over the past three seasons. The winner will proceed to Confederation Cup group stage. It is also a wonder that Gor technically did not have a coach. Social media giant cites the risk of further violence following the assault on the US Capitol by his supporters During his four years in office, Trump used Twitter to ridicule his political opponents, labelling them with mocking nicknames. This comes after his repeated rejection of the election result and violent protests by his supporters.